.TH RPITALK-CONFIG 8 "February 2026" "rpitalk" "System Administration Commands"

.SH NAME
rpitalk-config \- interactive configuration tool for RPITalk emulator

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rpitalk-config

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rpitalk-config
is an interactive configuration script for the RPITalk hardware speech
synthesizer emulator.

It reads default values from
.I /etc/rpitalk/emulator.conf
and prompts the user to select:

.RS
.IP \(bu 2
which synthesizer to emulate (DECtalk or LiteTalk)
.IP \(bu
which serial port to use
.IP \(bu
the debug verbosity level
.RE

After collecting user input,
.B rpitalk-config
updates the following configuration files while preserving comments:

.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.I /etc/rpitalk/emulator.conf
.IP \(bu
.I /etc/rpitalk/gadget.conf
.RE

If the selected port is
.BR ttyGS0 ,
USB gadget mode is enabled automatically in
.I /etc/rpitalk/gadget.conf .
For other ports, gadget mode is disabled.

.SH CONFIGURATION FILES

.TP
.I /etc/rpitalk/emulator.conf
Main configuration file for the emulator. The following keys are updated:

.RS
.TP
.B emulate
Which synthesizer to emulate: \fBdectlk\fR or \fBltlk\fR.
.TP
.B port
Serial port device name (for example, \fBttyGS0\fR or \fBttyUSB0\fR).
.TP
.B debug
Debug verbosity level (0 to 3).
.RE

.TP
.I /etc/rpitalk/gadget.conf
USB gadget configuration file. The following keys are updated:

.RS
.TP
.B ENABLE_GADGET
Set to 1 if the selected port is \fBttyGS0\fR, otherwise 0.
.TP
.B PRODUCT_ID
USB product ID corresponding to the selected emulation type.
.TP
.B SERIAL
USB serial number string.
.TP
.B PRODUCT
USB product description string.
.RE

.SH INTERACTIVE OPERATION
When run, the program:

.RS
.IP 1. 3
Reads defaults from
.I /etc/rpitalk/emulator.conf .
.IP 2.
Prompts for an emulation type (1 = DECtalk, 2 = LiteTalk).
.IP 3.
Prompts for a serial port name.
.IP 4.
Prompts for a debug level (0 to 3).
.IP 5.
Writes the updated values to the configuration files.
.RE

.SH EXAMPLES
Run the configuration tool:

.PP
.nf
rpitalk-config
.fi

.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/rpitalk/emulator.conf
RPITalk emulator configuration file.

.TP
.I /etc/rpitalk/gadget.conf
RPITalk USB gadget configuration file.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rpitalk-emulator (1),
.BR speech-dispatcher (1)

